Part 2: OLS Outputs

X

get_X <- function(df, n, p) {
  rawX <- df[c(1:p)]
  rawX['ones'] = rep(1, n)
  return (as.matrix(rawX[c(p+1, c(1:p))]))
}
X <- get_X(cars,length(cars$hp), 3)

Assumption: X has full rank

get_betahats <- function(X, y) {
  return (solve( t(X) %*% X ) %*% t(X) %*% y)
}

Part 3: QR Decomposition

qr_ols <- function(X, y) {
  QRD <- qr(X)
  Q <- qr.Q(QRD)
  R <- qr.R(QRD)
  QTy <- t(Q) %*% y
  return (backsolve(r=R, QTy, upper.tri=TRUE))
}

b <- qr_ols(X, y)
b
##             [,1]
## [1,] 27.61052686
## [2,] -0.01782227
## [3,]  0.51083369
## [4,] -4.35879720
